Why can't they just love each other, without these thoughts being present? And I'm getting way to autistic about this here, but I disagree that this isn't coming from a place of fear from this guy. Why would he otherwise think this even, instead of just knowing that she is not for real and just pretending, as she clearly loves him. This is all symptomatic of this beta mindset. And in general it just feels like Herio's works are going the wrong direction.
